# Mormon Bridge - Godot/GDScript Project Rules

## Language and Framework
- This is a Godot game project using GDScript
- Always use GDScript syntax when writing or modifying `.gd` files
- Refer to official Godot documentation and GDScript documentation when implementing features
- Follow Godot best practices for signals, nodes, scenes, and resource management

## Code Style
- Use TABS for indentation in all `.gd` (GDScript) and `.tscn` (Godot scene) files
- Tab size: 4 spaces equivalent
- Follow GDScript naming conventions:
  - snake_case for variables, functions, and file names
  - PascalCase for class names
  - SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Use ASCII characters for quotes, dashes, and punctuation unless specifically required (e.g., use " and ' not " " ' ', use - not – or —)

## Resources
- Godot Docs: https://docs.godotengine.org/
- GDScript Reference: https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/tutorials/scripting/gdscript/

